<subSubSection id="C374652CFFBAFFD1D4CCFB2D0DA1FAA2" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFBAFFD1D4CCFB2D0DA1FAA2" blockId="71.[151,1437,1014,2013]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFBAFFD1D4CCFB2D0C1AFB33" bold="true" box="[199,322,1158,1184]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFBAFFD1D5BEFB2C0F29FB33" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano, 2022" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano" authorityYear="2022" box="[437,625,1159,1185]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caqueta" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFBAFFD1D5BEFB2C0F29FB33" box="[437,625,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Tenedos caqueta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFBAFFD1D672FB2C0FE2FB32" bold="true" box="[633,698,1159,1185]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22957CEFFBAFFD1D672FB2C0FE2FB32" box="[633,698,1159,1185]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, are distinguished from remain species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFBAFFD1D096FB2C085BFB32" authorityName="Jocque &amp; Baert" authorityYear="2002" box="[1181,1283,1159,1185]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barronus">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFBAFFD1D096FB2C085BFB32" box="[1181,1283,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">barronus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by extremely developed conductor (C), apically rounded anterior margin; large, bifid median apophysis (MA) with apically rounded branches; large, complex retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA), posterior branch (pRTA) with groove on its extension, anterior branch (aRTA) very thin; wide, small basal retrolateral tibial apophysis (bRTA) (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFBAFFD1D11BFB5808CFFA9E" box="[1296,1431,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 49" captionStartId="72.[151,250,1691,1715]" captionTargetBox="[151,1408,489,1661]" captionTargetId="figure-140@72.[151,1436,489,1668]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="FIGURE 49. Tenedos caqueta sp. n. A–B. Male habits (LEUA-00000035889):A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–F. Male palp: C. Ventral view. D. Prolateral. E. Retroventral view. F. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm; C–F: 300µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520900/files/figure.png" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Figs 49C–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFBAFFD1D49CFABD0DB5FAA2" box="[151,237,1302,1329]" captionStart="FIGURE 50" captionStartId="73.[151,250,1839,1863]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,190,1815]" captionTargetId="figure-19@73.[151,1436,181,1815]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURE 50. Tenedos calebi sp. n. A–B. Male palp (ICN-Ar-10935): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. Tenedos caqueta sp. n. C–D. Male palp (LEUA-00000035889): C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–D: 200µm. Abbreviations: aMA, anterior branch of the median apophysis; ApC, appendix of the conductor; aRTA, anterior branch of the retrolateral tibial apophysis; bRTA, basal retrolateral tibial apophysis; C, conductor; E, embolus; pRTA, posterior branch of the retrolateral tibial apophysis; pMA, posterior branch of the median apophysis; SD, spermatic ducts; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520902/files/figure.png" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">50C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
